  "texts": [
    "The integration of Llama 2 7b with the Google Query API serves as a concrete example of how LLMs can be evolved beyond static training datasets to interact with the ever-changing landscape of global information.",
    "Moreover, this integration highlights the importance of addressing the ethical and practical challenges that arise with API dependency, including data bias, privacy concerns, and the need for robust fallback mechanisms.",
    "These considerations are crucial for the responsible development and deployment of enhanced LLMs in real-world applications.The successful augmentation of Llama 2 7b with the Google Query API marks a significant milestone in the quest to develop more accurate, reliable, and ethically responsible LLMs.",
    "This study not only contributes to the academic discourse on LLM enhancement but also offers practical insights for model developers aiming to leverage external data sources.",
    "Looking forward, the integration of LLMs with real-time data APIs holds immense potential for transforming how we develop, deploy, and interact with AI in the pursuit of knowledge, making this an exciting area for future research and development.json() def process_input(input_text): # Evaluate need for external info if needs_external_info(input_text): query = construct_query(input_text) api_response = query_google_api(query) refined_response = parse_response(api_response) # Integrate response into text generation output_text = generate_text(refined_response) return output_text else: # Proceed with internal text generation return generate_text(input_text) # Example usage input_text = \"The world's tallest building?\""
  ],
